author: stsp
msg: Bring merge test 132 ("replace that causes a tree-conflict") one step
closer to passing, by fixing the duplicated tree conflict notifications
which the test triggered. The test still fails because it skips an item
unexpectedly.
* subversion/libsvn_client/repos_diff.c
(add_directory): Really catch the case where the node being replaced is
already tree-conflicted. The action recorded for a tree-conflicted
item (which we previously attempted to delete) is 'tree_conflicted',
not 'deleted'. Also, since we're about to send notification about
a tree conflict victim, the current item is also marked 'tree_conflicted',
and not 'added'. So the set of action combinations which consitute a
replace is not just "[add] vs. [delete]", but "[tree_conflicted | add]
vs. [tree_conflicted | delete]." And maybe there are even more? Not sure,
leave a comment asking this question. This bug shows how badly we are in
need of atomic replace callbacks in the editor interface.
